=== Parliamentary QA ===
Title: Stronger Penalties for Importers and Distributors of Vapes
Date: 2025-09-23
Source: Singapore Parliament
Document Type: Parliamentary QA (Written Answer)
Topic: Vaping, Etomidate, Legislation, Enforcement

Summary:
- Question about whether importers and distributors of vapes will face penalties equivalent to etomidate-laced vape importers, given that one-third of confiscated vapes tested positive for etomidate.
- Ministry of Health (MOH) response: reviewing longer-term legislation to adapt to new e-vaporiser landscape; new legislation planned for enactment in Q1 2026.

Key Entities:
- Ministry of Health (MOH)
- Coordinating Minister for Social Policies and Minister for Health
- Mr Sharael Taha, MP (Pasir Ris-Changi GRC)
- Vape importers and distributors
- Etomidate-laced vape importers

Key Concepts:
- Review of penalties for suppliers of e-vaporisers
- Potential legislative update for all types of vapes
- Enforcement adaptation to changing substance landscape
- Legislative enactment timeline: Q1 2026

Body:
1. Question addressed regarding potential stronger deterrence for importers/distributors of regular vapes to match etomidate vape penalties.
2. Ministry of Health is reviewing legislative measures for e-vaporisers.
3. New legislation to include appropriate penalties for suppliers of all kinds of e-vaporisers.
4. Planned enactment: first quarter of 2026.

Author / Issuer:
Ministry of Health (MOH)
Date of Issue: 2025-09-23
